comments.content: it is my understanding that p2p pubsub actually slows down after the network scales beyond a few hundred users
comments.title: dispute this

comments.content:
No, it's a gossip protocol, each peer is only connected to XX peers, no matter how many total peers there are. Even if there was billions of peers, if each peer forwards each message to the XX peers they know, it only takes a few hops (ie a few seconds) for each message to propagate to billions of peers. 50×50×50×50×50 = 3125000000. Each hop might take a few hundred ms or less.
The more real peers there are, the more difficult and expensive it becomes to perform attacks to slow down the pubsub. It can't really be stopped, only slowed down.
